# Solvus Protocol — Agent Rules for Cursor / Windsurf
# Copy file này thành .cursorrules hoặc .windsurfrules tại project root.

## MANDATORY INITIALIZATION — Đọc trước mọi task

Before responding to ANY request in this project:
1. Read `.agent/AGENT_RULES.md` completely
2. Read `.agent/PROJECT_MAP.md` — locate affected modules  
3. Read `.agent/INVARIANTS.md` — identify relevant invariants
4. Read `.agent/GRAVEYARD.md` — confirm no deprecated patterns will be recreated

Do NOT skip this step even for "simple" tasks. In a ZK cryptography project, a single
wrong byte silently breaks proof generation.

---

## CRITICAL PROJECT CONTEXT

This is a ZK (Zero-Knowledge) cryptography project — Solvus Protocol.
- Language stack: TypeScript (Client/Relayer) + Noir (ZK Circuit) + Cairo (Smart Contract)
- Three layers must stay in EXACT sync — any divergence = proof fail with no clear error
- Most dangerous failure mode: silent failure (proof generation fails with "unsatisfied constraint")

---

## ABSOLUTE PROHIBITIONS

NEVER do these without explicit instruction AND reading INVARIANTS.md:
- Change Poseidon input order: must be [secret, x_hi, x_lo, badge_type]
- Change timestamp source: must be relayerResponse.timestamp, NOT Date.now()
- Make buildProverInputs() synchronous: it MUST be async, callers MUST await
- Expose pubkey_x or pubkey_y outside Noir circuit (privacy violation)
- Use Buffer.allocUnsafe() anywhere
- Use bitwise | or & for boolean logic in TypeScript or Cairo
- Change BN254_PRIME value or format (must be decimal bigint literal)
- Change circomlibjs version (must be EXACTLY 0.1.7, no ^ or ~)
- Create files that exist in .agent/GRAVEYARD.md
- Create new files without checking .agent/PROJECT_MAP.md first

---

## MANDATORY POST-TASK CHECKLIST

After EVERY code change, confirm:
[ ] Updated .agent/PROJECT_MAP.md if file structure changed
[ ] Updated .agent/STACK.md if dependencies changed  
[ ] Appended to .agent/SESSION_LOG.md
[ ] Ran consistency checks:
    - npx tsc --noEmit
    - grep -rn "allocUnsafe\|Date\.now()" packages/core/prover/ packages/core/client/
    - grep -rn " | \| & " packages/ cairo/ (check for bitwise operators)

---

## THREE-LAYER SYNC REQUIREMENT

When modifying anything related to:
- Threshold values → update BOTH TypeScript getThresholdForBadge() AND Cairo get_expected_constraints()
- Poseidon hash → verify BOTH circomlibjs output AND Noir hash_4 output match
- Field encoding → verify BOTH felt252ToU8Array32() TS AND serialize_felt_to_u8_32() Cairo match
- pubkey split → verify BOTH splitTo128BitFields() TS AND split_to_128bit_fields() Noir match

---

